		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />.... Is there any way you can find out if the TV is decoding the video as NTSC-M vs PAL-M ? Showing just purple and green is the axis from +U+V to -U-V in YUV; maybe PAL chroma subsampling is canceling out the +U-V to -U+V axis???  Maybe the TV automatically detects standard based on whether the colorburst is 3.579MHz vs 3.576MHz ?????<br /><br />Feels like a huge stretch, tho.

		

		</td>
